SIMPLE: profess
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Profess
<hw>Pro*fess"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Professed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Professing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>prof⟦egrave⟧s</ets>, masc., <ets>professe</ets>, fem., professed
(monk or nun), L. <ets>professus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>profiteri</ets> to
profess; <ets>pro</ets> before, forward + <ets>fateri</ets> to confess,
own. See <er>Confess</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To make open declaration of, as of one's knowledge,
belief, action, etc.; to avow or acknowledge; to confess publicly; to
own or admit freely.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Hear me <xex>profess</xex>
sincerely.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The best and wisest of them all <qex>professed</qex>⟦br⟧
To know this only, that he nothing knew.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1144 --></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To set up a claim to; to make presence to; hence, to
put on or present an appearance of.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I do <qex>profess</qex> to be no less than I seem.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To present to knowledge of, to proclaim one's self
versed in; to make one's self a teacher or practitioner of, to set up as
an authority respecting; to declare (one's self to be such); <as>as, he
<ex>professes</ex> surgery; to <ex>profess</ex> one's self a
physician.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Profess</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Profess
<hw>Pro*fess"</hw> <pr>(pr⟦osl⟧*f⟦ecr⟧s")</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To take a profession upon one's self by a public
declaration; to confess.</def> <rj><au>Drayton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To declare friendship.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Professed</ent>⟦br⟧
